        "created_at": "2025-01-17T15:08:22.054Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hey,</p>\n<p>I use Signal a lot and for a long time now (when there were no disappearing messages). There are a lot of old/temporary groups/messages/media that blow up my Signal backups. What’s the best way to clean up (especially old/unused groups)?</p>\n<p>There are two things to do:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>leave group</li>\n<li>delete group chat</li>\n</ol>\n<p>I thought I’m smart and used the new chat folder feature:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>show only “Groups”</li>\n<li>scroll the long list to the end (there are the old/unused groups)</li>\n<li>click on a group chat</li>\n<li>click on the name at the top =&gt; Leave group</li>\n</ol>\n<p>At this point</p>\n<ul>\n<li>I’m not part of the group any more (GOOD). The chat is not listed in the “Groups” chat folder anymore (WEIRD)</li>\n<li>But the chat was not deleted</li>\n<li>I can search for the group. I can find it in the search results.</li>\n<li>If I click on the group I can not delete it (this is only available with long tap =&gt; delete in the list view)</li>\n<li>The long tap options menu (to delete the group) is not available for the search results (THIS IS A BUG IMO)</li>\n<li>So I have to scroll down <strong>everything</strong> to find it (not realistic) and then I can: log tap =&gt; Delete</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This is a terrible UX :(</p>\n<p>At the same point:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>When I use the chat folder filter: “Groups” only</li>\n<li>Scroll down</li>\n<li>There are groups where I’m not a member of any more</li>\n<li>THIS IS INCONSISTENT</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I hope you understand what I want to say.</p>\n<p>To clarify my motivation: Cops/Cellebrite are able to break a lot of phones nowerdays. We should help people to make it easy for them to delete old messages.</p>\n<p>It would be nice to have a auto cleanup feature, like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>show groups which were not used for time X</li>\n<li>show (big) chats with a lot of messages/media data</li>\n<li>auto delete groups (disappering groups)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>What do you say?</p>",
